# Lower-central support for integral Hall-Witt strict tails

The multidegree bound for the explicit integral Hall-Witt strict trace has a
direct semantic consequence.  If `x`, `y`, and `z` lie in lower-central
layers indexed by positive one-based weights, then every retained strict
factor lies one layer above the parent triple.

