/-!
# Routing recurrences for Hall-Witt cutoff multiplicities

The integral Hall-Witt strict tail has coefficient-independent finite support
below every fixed cutoff.  This file connects those fixed-slot coordinates to
the scalar recurrence for stable rightward routing.

Modulo cutoff, moving one current word rightward adds the bracketed correction
profile to the old higher profile.  Every current Hall-Witt word has unit-label
weight three, so iterating the strict correction operator `cutoff` times is
uniformly invisible below that cutoff.

