/-!
# Fixed-slot vectors for Hall-Witt cutoff routing

Below one cutoff, Hall-Witt routing has a fixed finite formal vocabulary.
Package the multiplicities of an arbitrary trace in those slots, prove the
pointwise vector recurrences for rightward routing, and show that the vector
is complete up to permutation for supported below-cutoff traces.

