/-!
# Polynomial first-pass Hall-Witt residual profiles

The positive and negative Hall-Witt first routing passes each compile to
three polynomially repeated fixed affine packets.  Apply the variable-input
composition theorem three times, starting from the zero cutoff profile.

Every retained formal slot in either literal first-pass output is therefore
an integer-valued polynomial in the natural multiplicity, with the uniform
degree bound `cutoff + (cutoff + cutoff)`.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
