Every fixed retained slot produced by repeatedly routing one Hall-Witt current
word has a cutoff-bounded integer-valued polynomial multiplicity.  Normalize
that polynomial into the repository's explicit repeated-block recipe
language, and collect the resulting expansions over the finite cutoff
vocabulary.

