/-!
# Explicit empty-tail orbit prefixes for Hall-Witt outer packets

The inhomogeneous part of a triangular outer-packet trace substitution is the
orbit emitted from the empty tail.  It is the ordered concatenation of the
homogeneous iterates of the fixed emitted prefix.  This file records that
range-based normal form and specializes it to the positive and negative
Hall-Witt packet traces.

