/-!
# Triangular active subsequences for bounded Hall-Witt depth words

When a substituted word contributes an output subsequence, discard source
positions whose packet contributes the empty subsequence.  Every remaining
source position contributes a nonempty packet subsequence.

For the bounded Hall-Witt depth substitution, the retained singleton is the
unique rank-preserving choice.  Every other active choice strictly raises the
rank `sum (depth + 1)`.  This is the triangular kernel needed for a
polynomial recurrence on ordered subsequence multiplicities.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

