/-!
# Polynomial subsequence coordinates for bounded depth-retained schedules

A bounded depth-retained schedule is the bounded depth word flattened through
one fixed retained transition packet at each depth. Regroup a selected
transition subword by the active source depths whose packets contribute a
nonempty subsequence. Only finitely many bounded source depth words of length
at most the target length occur.

