Crossing over a fixed carried trace concatenates one bounded depth-crossing
schedule for each carried word.  Ordered subsequence multiplicity across a
concatenation is the convolution over the suffixes of the requested word.
Consequently, the fixed finite concatenation still has polynomial transition
subword coordinates, and hence polynomial bounded affine-term coordinates.

