/-!
# Repeated-block normal forms for Hall-Witt middle first-route programs

Literal rightward movement distributes over concatenation.  The middle
first-route programs are therefore repetitions of one moved singleton block,
rather than one opaque movement across a repeated trace.

This exposes the diagonal repeated-block boundary needed by the outer-packet
symbolic recollection compiler.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

