/-!
# Polynomial bounded terms for crossed empty-orbit prefixes

The crossed empty-orbit schedule has polynomial ordered-subsequence coordinates.
Every bounded affine-constant coordinate is therefore a finite sum of those
coordinates, indexed by its possible constant-producing transition.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
