/-!
# Polynomial Hall-Witt packet affine orbit endpoints

The ordinary second-route compiler of an emitted Hall-Witt orbit prefix is a
retained transition schedule. The retained bounded-depth collector supplies
polynomial slot coordinates for that schedule. Its compiled endpoint is also
cutoff-vocabulary-supported because every literal `ofTrace` affine compiler
preserves the finite vocabulary.

These two facts discharge the unshifted endpoint hypotheses of the
successor-origin reduction and therefore yield unconditional global positive
and negative strict-tail cutoff-profile polynomiality.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
