/-!
# Substitute reconstructed Hall-Witt strict-tail cutoff profiles

The signed global Newton recipes reconstruct the formal Hall-Witt strict-tail
profile below a unit-label cutoff.  After replacing the six formal labels by
arbitrary positive-weight commutator words, that reconstructed profile still
recovers the physically retained substituted strict trace.

The key point is monotonicity: binding positive-weight words cannot decrease
weight.  Hence a substituted occurrence that survives the physical cutoff
already survived the formal unit-label cutoff.

