/-!
# Recollecting concrete Hall-Witt strict-tail residual sources

The concrete Hall-coordinate strict-tail theorem identifies the complete
fixed-weight Hall segment of a Hall-Witt tail and proves that the remaining
value starts one lower-central stratum higher.  An operational symbolic
collector still needs an exact symbolic source for that remaining value.

This file packages that boundary precisely.  A residual-source certificate
records such an exact symbolic source without pretending that the coarse
global Newton bound is already the physical Hall weight of each operational
factor.  Any semantic normalizer at the residual's physical support stratum
then recollects the certified source into an evaluation-equivalent source
supported one stratum higher.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

