/-!
# Physical joint-weight bounds for substituted strict-tail slots

An exact formal slot recipe has degree bounded by its unit-label weight.  If
every substituted atom has physical weight at least `inputWeight`, binding a
formal slot multiplies that lower bound by `inputWeight`.  Collision sums for
one concrete word therefore have degree at most the physical word weight
divided by `inputWeight`.

