/-!
# Repeated-block expansions for fixed affine Hall-Witt packets

The fixed-packet affine compiler gives a cutoff-bounded integer-valued
polynomial for every retained formal slot.  Normalize those polynomials into
the repository's explicit repeated-block recipe language and assemble the
coordinates over the ordered finite cutoff vocabulary.

Unlike the earlier one-word expansion, this adapter handles an arbitrary fixed
stable-routing packet, including its accumulated affine constant.

The file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

